# Specialty Microwave Corp 8682-500

## About

The **Specialty Microwave Corp 8682-500** is a remotely controlled 1:4 Protection Switch designed for RF redundancy and signal-path protection in critical microwave receive systems. It allows up to four Low Noise Amplifiers (LNAs) to be managed and protected through an integrated relay and detection system.

The unit continuously monitors LNA health, switch positions, and power supply conditions, automatically redirecting the signal path in the event of a detected LNA failure. Operators can also place the device in manual mode for direct control of each switch position.

The **8682-500** is typically deployed in satellite earth stations, RF distribution networks, and other environments where uninterrupted LNA availability is essential.

## Key Features

- Ability to monitor the positions of all the switches.
- Ability to monitor the status of the HPA's
- Ability to toggle between positions for the 4 available switches. 
- Ability to change the device from automatic to manual mode.

